' summary of problem:
' if word-wrap is enabled (lp=1), outputting cursor-left or backspace does not
' decrement column position, forcing unwanted word-wrap at the position of the
' box as shown here. see /core/tests/test-word-wrap-column-decrement.lbl

' testing some MCI in the editor like the following could work:
' £s1£o-£ho£h4
' 1) [.M]CI Read in editor
' 2) Alt-H to enable monitor
' 3) w store <memory_location>
' 4) x
' 5) <Return> to do MCI Read
' 6) observe X register value in this register dump:
'    - A:0D X:00 Y:01

' - also try:
' £p0£o>£p6£o<

' separate issue: print modes - what "s.menu 3" says:
' £p0: normal printing
' £p1:
' £p2:
' £p3: character, backspace
' £p4: space, character, 2 backspaces, character
' £p5: character, bell
' £p6: character, 2 cursor lefts [left]
' £p7: character, cursor left, cursor up [up]
' £p8: character, cursor left, cursor down [down]

' menu does not include these print modes:
' £p9: character, cursor down [diagonal: up -> down, left -> right]
' £pj:

' to enable memory location write watch in monitor:
' w store $03bc

' disable 1 ; disable breakpoint on write
' enable 1 ; re-enable breakpoint

